            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Ego <persName ref="#people/4252">Guilielmus cognomine Pinzone</persName>, ad
                        salutem et remedium animarum <rs key="#parentOf">patris et matris</rs> mee,
                        et mee, cum voluntate et consensu <rs key="#dominus/seniorOf">dominorum</rs>
                        meorum, videlicet domni <persName key="#Princeps #dominus/seniorOf"
                            ref="#people/3010">secundi Richardi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">principis</rs> et <persName key="#dominus/seniorOf"
                            ref="#people/3020">Roberti de Medania</persName>, do, trado atque offero
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/3001">Sancti Blasii
                            martiris Christi</orgName>, sito prope <rs key="#Walls">murum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities #Walls" ref="#places/4000">Aversane</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">urbis</rs>, in quo domna <persName
                            key="#Abbesses #Personal_rank" ref="#people/3081">Mansa</persName>
                        <rs key="#Personal_rank">venerabilis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Abbesses">abbatissa</rs> preest, integram <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >unam petiam</rs> terre, que est in loco ubi dicitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/4024" key="#Villages/settlements #Petiae">ad
                            Cupuli</placeName>, qui sunt <rs key="#Size">modios terre viginti
                            duo</rs>, rationabiliter mensurata, habetque hos <rs key="#Fines"
                            >fines</rs>: ab uno latere est finis terra, quam modo residetur ab
                        Herberto Bardone; ab alio vero latere est fìnis terra, que modo retinet
                        Roggerius, fìlius Turgisi; ab uno capite est finis <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Roads">via
                            publica</rs>; ab alio vero latere est finis terra predicti Roggerii et
                        terram unius villani sui. Hec autem predicta petia de terra, per prescriptos
                        fines et mensuras, una cum omnibus...</ab>
